body:
_From @maxpaj on October 22, 2018 14:2_

Running the example but changing the base for the Dockerfile to node:10-slim instead of node:8-slim breaks sourcemaps:

![1](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4847378/47296735-79252400-d613-11e8-8ade-0edb18c87227.PNG)

<details><summary>(code for searchability)</summary>
<p>

```
(function (exports, require, module, __filename, __dirname) { "use strict";
exports.__esModule = true;
var http = require("http");
var reqCnt = 1;
http.createServer(function (req, res) {
    var message = "Request Count: " + reqCnt;
    res.writeHead(200, { 'Content-Type': 'text/html' });
    res.end("<html><head><meta http-equiv=\"refresh\" content=\"2\"></head><body>" + message + "</body></html>");
    console.log("handled request: " + reqCnt++);
}).listen(3000);
console.log('server running on port 3000');
//# sourceMappingURL=index.js.map
});
```
</p>
</details>

![2](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4847378/47296736-79252400-d613-11e8-9d9c-00aafc53e39f.PNG)


However, my generated dist/index.js does not look the same as where the code breaks:
![3](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4847378/47296984-2ac45500-d614-11e8-8d90-6c8e6846ebec.PNG)

I made no other change to the files except that one line in the Dockerfile (`FROM node:10-slim`).

Possibly, the culprit is that the `//# sourceMappingURL=` no longer is at the last row in the file. However, I have no idea where this generated JS comes from or why it wraps the code in a `(function() { ... })();`

```
maxpaj@maxpaj-VirtualBox:~$ node -v
v10.12.0
maxpaj@maxpaj-VirtualBox:~$ docker -v
Docker version 18.06.0-ce, build 0ffa825
maxpaj@maxpaj-VirtualBox:~$ docker-compose -v
docker-compose version 1.22.0, build f46880fe
maxpaj@maxpaj-VirtualBox:~$ tsc -v
Version 3.1.3
maxpaj@maxpaj-VirtualBox:~$ vscode -v
1.28.2
7f3ce96ff4729c91352ae6def877e59c561f4850
x64
maxpaj@maxpaj-VirtualBox:~$ uname -a
Linux maxpaj-VirtualBox 4.15.0-36-generic #39~16.04.1-Ubuntu SMP Tue Sep 25 08:59:23 UTC 2018 x86_64 x86_64 x86_64 GNU/Linux
```

**The example works fine on my machine setup with node:8-slim.** 

I'm experiencing the exact same behaviour in my own project.

_Copied from original issue: Microsoft/vscode-recipes#156_
